wlBaseCfgTable.name: wlBaseCfgTable
wlBaseCfgTable.description: Table of basic Wireless Adapter Configuration objects.

wlBaseCfgEntry.name: wlBaseCfgEntry
wlBaseCfgEntry.description: Table of entries of basic Wireless Adapter Configuration objects.

wlBaseCfgEnable.name: wlBaseCfgEnable
wlBaseCfgEnable.description: Enable or disable the wireless adapter.

wlBaseCfgChannel.name: wlBaseCfgChannel
wlBaseCfgChannel.description: The configured wifi channel number or 'auto' for automatic selection of a channel with low interference.

wlBaseCfgCurrentChannel.name: wlBaseCfgCurrentChannel
wlBaseCfgCurrentChannel.description: The actual wifi channel number in use.

wlBaseCfgAutoScanTimer.name: wlBaseCfgAutoScanTimer
wlBaseCfgAutoScanTimer.description: When configured for auto mode, this timer value specifies how often to re-analyze the spectrum to select a low interference channel. Note: auto channel rescan will only occur when there are no actively connected devices.

wlBaseCfgMimoNEwc.name: wlBaseCfgMimoNEwc
wlBaseCfgMimoNEwc.description: Radio 802.11n Enhanced Wireless Consortium (EWC) mode: auto(1) disable(2)

wlBaseCfgMimoNRate.name: wlBaseCfgMimoNRate
wlBaseCfgMimoNRate.description: The configured Multiple Input Multiple Output (MIMO) 802.11n rate. Enumeration of: auto(1), use54g(2), rate6Dot5(3), rate13(4), rate19Dot5(5), rate26(6), rate39(7), rate52(8), rate58Dot5(9), rate65(10), rate78(11), rate104(12), rate117(13), rate130(14)

wlBaseCfgMimoNProtection.name: wlBaseCfgMimoNProtection
wlBaseCfgMimoNProtection.description: Multiple Input Multiple Output(MIMO) 802.11n protection mode. Enumeration of: off(1), auto(2),

wlBaseCfgNClientsOnly.name: wlBaseCfgNClientsOnly
wlBaseCfgNClientsOnly.description: Enable or disable the restriction of access to 802.11n clients, only. When enabled, prevent 802.11b/g clients from connecting.

wlBaseCfg54gRate.name: wlBaseCfg54gRate
wlBaseCfg54gRate.description: The rate when the radio is operating in 802.11g mode. This object only applies when the Multiple Input Multiple Output (MIMO) 802.11n Rate is set to use54g(2). Enumeration of: rate1M(1), rate2M(2), rate5Dot5M(3), rate6M(4), rate9M(5), rate11M(6), rate12M(7), rate18M(8), rate24M(9), rate36M(10), rate48M(11), rate54M(12)

wlBaseCfgMulticastRate.name: wlBaseCfgMulticastRate
wlBaseCfgMulticastRate.description: The rate for multicast traffic. Enumeration of: rate1M(1), rate2M(2), rate5Dot5M(3), rate6M(4), rate9M(5), rate11M(6), rate12M(7), rate18M(8), rate24M(9), rate36M(10), rate48M(11), rate54M(12)

wlBaseCfgBasicRate.name: wlBaseCfgBasicRate
wlBaseCfgBasicRate.description: The rate when the radio is operating in basic 802.11b/g mode. Enumeration of: default(1), -- use the factory defaulted basic rate all(2), -- allow all supported basic rates rate1And2(3), -- restrict the basic rates to 1Mbps and 2Mbps stdRates(4) -- restrict the basic rates to the standard rates of -- 1Mbps, 2Mbps, 5.5Mbps, 6Mbps, 11Mbps, 12Mbps, 24Mbps

wlBaseCfgFragThreshold.name: wlBaseCfgFragThreshold
wlBaseCfgFragThreshold.description: The threshold at which packets are fragmented.

wlBaseCfgRTSThreshold.name: wlBaseCfgRTSThreshold
wlBaseCfgRTSThreshold.description: The packet size of a request-to-send (RTS) transmission. A low threshold implies RTS packets are sent more frequently, thus requiring more bandwidth but ensuring packet transmission on a busy network.

wlBaseCfgDTIMInterval.name: wlBaseCfgDTIMInterval
wlBaseCfgDTIMInterval.description: The interval at which Delivery Traffic Indication Messages (DTIM) are generated. A DTIM message notifies a wireless client that a packet is waiting for tranmission.

wlBaseCfgBeaconInterval.name: wlBaseCfgBeaconInterval
wlBaseCfgBeaconInterval.description: The interval at which Beacons are generated.

wlBaseCfgGlobalMaxClients.name: wlBaseCfgGlobalMaxClients
wlBaseCfgGlobalMaxClients.description: The maximum number of wireless client devices that may be simultaneously connected to the radio. This value should include the sum total of all clients on all active SSIDs.

wlBaseCfgXPress.name: wlBaseCfgXPress
wlBaseCfgXPress.description: Enable or disable the XPress(TM) Technology.

wlBaseCfgTxPowerPercent.name: wlBaseCfgTxPowerPercent
wlBaseCfgTxPowerPercent.description: The percentage of total power that should be used for data transmissions.

wlBaseCfgWMMEnable.name: wlBaseCfgWMMEnable
wlBaseCfgWMMEnable.description: Enable or disable Wifi Multimedia. When set to TRUE, audio, video and voice application data is prioritized over other network traffic.

wlBaseCfgWMMNoAck.name: wlBaseCfgWMMNoAck
wlBaseCfgWMMNoAck.description: Enable or disable the suppression of acknowledgements for frames that do not require a QOS Acknowledgement. This avoids the unnecessary transmission of acknowledgements for highly time-critical data.

wlBaseCfgWMMApsd.name: wlBaseCfgWMMApsd
wlBaseCfgWMMApsd.description: Enable or disable the Automatic Power Save Delivery (APSD) power management method. This feature is useful for bi-directional applications, such as VoIp phones.

wlBaseCfgWpsAddClientMethod.name: wlBaseCfgWpsAddClientMethod
wlBaseCfgWpsAddClientMethod.description: Configure the method of adding Clients: pushButton(1), accessPointPIN(2), stationPIN(3)

wlBaseCfgWpsApMode.name: wlBaseCfgWpsApMode
wlBaseCfgWpsApMode.description: Enable or disable WiFi Protected Setup (WPS) AP mode. If your provider is using an external registrar for security, select true(1). The PIN for AP mode is specified by the registrar. Provide this PIN to the client. Select wlBaseCfgWpsConfigAp to begin the registration process with the client.

wlBaseCfgWpsConfigAp.name: wlBaseCfgWpsConfigAp
wlBaseCfgWpsConfigAp.description: Start AP configuration. If your provider is using an external registrar for security, wlBaseCfgWpsApMode then select true(1) to begin the registration process with the client.

wlBaseCfgWpsDevicePIN.name: wlBaseCfgWpsDevicePIN
wlBaseCfgWpsDevicePIN.description: Device PIN provided by external registrar.

wlBaseCfgWpsAddEnrollee.name: wlBaseCfgWpsAddEnrollee
wlBaseCfgWpsAddEnrollee.description: Start AP configuration. If wlBaseCfgWpsAddClientMethod is set for pushButton(1), then the user must simultaneously push the WPS button on the rear panel of the wireless zNID and set this object to true(1) for push button registration on the client device.

wlBaseCfgBridgeRestrictMode.name: wlBaseCfgBridgeRestrictMode
wlBaseCfgBridgeRestrictMode.description: Configure the bridge restriction mode: enable(1), enableScan(2), disable(3),

wlBaseCfgBridgeRefresh.name: wlBaseCfgBridgeRefresh
wlBaseCfgBridgeRefresh.description: Scans for any wireless bridge devices in range and displays them in the Remote Bridge MAC Address table. Selecting true(1) will update the wireless bridge devices in range. Wait for a few seconds for the update.

wlVirtualIntfTable.name: wlVirtualIntfTable
wlVirtualIntfTable.description: Table of Wireless Virtual LAN Interface Configuration, Status and Statistics objects.

wlVirtualIntfEntry.name: wlVirtualIntfEntry
wlVirtualIntfEntry.description: Entries in Wireless Vitrual LAN Interface Table.

wlVirtualIndex.name: wlVirtualIndex
wlVirtualIndex.description: Basic access point interface index. Guest (or Virtual) access points begin with index = 2.

wlVirtualHide.name: wlVirtualHide
wlVirtualHide.description: Enable or disable the suppression of the advertising of the access point's SSID. If enabled, clients will need to configure the SSID to associate.

wlVirtualAPIsolation.name: wlVirtualAPIsolation
wlVirtualAPIsolation.description: Enable or disable the isolation of clients by enabling or disabling secure forwarding mode. This will preventpreventing one client from sending packets directly to another client. All packets are forwarded upstream on the WAN interface.

wlVirtualDisableWme.name: wlVirtualDisableWme
wlVirtualDisableWme.description: Enable or disable the Wireless Multi-Media mode.

wlVirtualEnableWmf.name: wlVirtualEnableWmf
wlVirtualEnableWmf.description: Enable or disable Wireless Multicast Forwarding.

wlVirtualSsid.name: wlVirtualSsid
wlVirtualSsid.description: Configure the Primary SSID assigned to the wl0 interface, or the Guest SSIDs assigned to the virtual wireless interfaces.

wlVirtualBssMacAddr.name: wlVirtualBssMacAddr
wlVirtualBssMacAddr.description: MAC Address assigned to the primary SSID.

wlVirtualCountryCode.name: wlVirtualCountryCode
wlVirtualCountryCode.description: Two character country code. The country code is automatically configured based upon the model number of the unit. All countries with 100mW EIRP maximum transmit power use the United Kingdom country code. North American models may use the maximum transmit power of 300mW EIRP.

wlVirtualMaxClients.name: wlVirtualMaxClients
wlVirtualMaxClients.description: Maximum number of client devices that may be simultaneously connected to this SSID. The maximum clients value assigned to each access points must not exceed the global maximum clients value.

wlVirtualEnable.name: wlVirtualEnable
wlVirtualEnable.description: Enable or disable a single Wireless Virtual LAN Interface

wlSecurityTable.name: wlSecurityTable
wlSecurityTable.description: Table of Wireless Security Configuration, Status and Statistics objects for virtual LAN interfaces.

wlSecurityEntry.name: wlSecurityEntry
wlSecurityEntry.description: Table of entries, per virtual LAN interface, of Wireless Security objects.

wlSecuritySsid.name: wlSecuritySsid
wlSecuritySsid.description: The primary SSID assigned to the wl0 interface, or the Guest SSIDs assigned to this virtual wireless interface.

wlSecurityWps.name: wlSecurityWps
wlSecurityWps.description: Enable or disable WiFi Protected Setup (WPS) security method. If WPS is disabled, the network authentication method, the data encryption, and network key should also be configured in order to authenticate to this wireless network.

wlSecurityAuthMode.name: wlSecurityAuthMode
wlSecurityAuthMode.description: Configure the network authentication method: mode8011x(1), open(2), shared(3), wpa(4), wpa2(5), wpaPsk(6), wpa2Psk(7), mixedWpa2Wpa(8), mixedWpa2WpaPsk(9)

wlSecurityWpaPsk.name: wlSecurityWpaPsk
wlSecurityWpaPsk.description: WPA/WPAI Passphrase. This field cannot contain a SPACE and is returned as a string of asterisks.

wlSecurityWpaMode.name: wlSecurityWpaMode
wlSecurityWpaMode.description: WPA/WAPI Encryption mode: tkip(1), aes(2), tkipAes(3)

wlSecurityWepStatus.name: wlSecurityWepStatus
wlSecurityWepStatus.description: Status of Wireless Encryption Protocol (WEP) encryption: disabled(1) enabled(2)

wlSecurityRadiusServerIP.name: wlSecurityRadiusServerIP
wlSecurityRadiusServerIP.description: IP address of the Remote Authentication Dial In User Server (RADIUS) used for 802.1x authentication.

wlSecurityRadiusPort.name: wlSecurityRadiusPort
wlSecurityRadiusPort.description: UDP port to use for accessing the Remote Authentication Dial In User Server (RADIUS).

wlSecurityRadiusKey.name: wlSecurityRadiusKey
wlSecurityRadiusKey.description: Remote Authentication Dial In User Server (RADIUS) authentication key. This field cannot contain a SPACE and is returned as a string of asterisks.

wlSecurityCurrentWepKeyIndex64.name: wlSecurityCurrentWepKeyIndex64
wlSecurityCurrentWepKeyIndex64.description: Index into array of 64-bit encryption keys.

wlSecurityCurrentWepKeyIndex128.name: wlSecurityCurrentWepKeyIndex128
wlSecurityCurrentWepKeyIndex128.description: Index into array of 128-bit encryption keys.

wlSecurityWep64Key1.name: wlSecurityWep64Key1
wlSecurityWep64Key1.description: WEP 64-bit encryption key 1 string, which must consist of 5 ASCII characters or 10 hexadecimal digits.

wlSecurityWep64Key2.name: wlSecurityWep64Key2
wlSecurityWep64Key2.description: WEP 64-bit encryption key 2 string, which must consist of 5 ASCII characters or 10 hexadecimal digits.

wlSecurityWep64Key3.name: wlSecurityWep64Key3
wlSecurityWep64Key3.description: WEP 64-bit encryption key 3 string, which must consist of 5 ASCII characters or 10 hexadecimal digits.

wlSecurityWep64Key4.name: wlSecurityWep64Key4
wlSecurityWep64Key4.description: WEP 64-bit encryption key 4 string, which must consist of 5 ASCII characters or 10 hexadecimal digits.

wlSecurityWep128Key1.name: wlSecurityWep128Key1
wlSecurityWep128Key1.description: WEP 128-bit encryption key 1 string, which must consist of 13 ASCII characters or 26 hexadecimal digits.

wlSecurityWep128Key2.name: wlSecurityWep128Key2
wlSecurityWep128Key2.description: WEP 128-bit encryption key 2 string, which must consist of 13 ASCII characters or 26 hexadecimal digits.

wlSecurityWep128Key3.name: wlSecurityWep128Key3
wlSecurityWep128Key3.description: WEP 128-bit encryption key 3 string, which must consist of 13 ASCII characters or 26 hexadecimal digits.

wlSecurityWep128Key4.name: wlSecurityWep128Key4
wlSecurityWep128Key4.description: WEP 128-bit encryption key 4 string, which must consist of 13 ASCII characters or 26 hexadecimal digits.

wlSecurityWpa2NetReauth.name: wlSecurityWpa2NetReauth
wlSecurityWpa2NetReauth.description: Configure the WPA2 network re-authentication time, in seconds.

wlSecurityMACFilterMode.name: wlSecurityMACFilterMode
wlSecurityMACFilterMode.description: Configure the MAC Filter mode. The MAC Filter rules defined in the wlMACFilterTable will be ignored when this object is set to disable(3).

wlMACFilterTable.name: wlMACFilterTable
wlMACFilterTable.description: Table of Wireless MAC filter rules for a virtual wireless interface. The MAC Filter table contains a list of MAC addresses for devices that are permitted to connect, or prevented from connecting to the wireless service.

wlMACFilterEntry.name: wlMACFilterEntry
wlMACFilterEntry.description: Entries in the Wireless MAC filter rules for a virtual wireless interface.

wlMACFilterIndex.name: wlMACFilterIndex
wlMACFilterIndex.description: The Wireless MAC filter table index.

wlMACFilterSsid.name: wlMACFilterSsid
wlMACFilterSsid.description: The primary SSID assigned to the wl0 interface, or the Guest SSIDs assigned to this virtual wireless interface.

wlMACFilterMacAddr.name: wlMACFilterMacAddr
wlMACFilterMacAddr.description: The MAC address which to apply to the filter rule.

wlMACFilterIfName.name: wlMACFilterIfName
wlMACFilterIfName.description: The virtual interface name to which this rule applies.

wlMACFilterRowStatus.name: wlMACFilterRowStatus
wlMACFilterRowStatus.description: The SNMP RowStatus of the current row. When creating a new MAC Filter entry for a virtual wireless interface, only the MAC Address must be specified. The wlVirtualIndex will be used to determine the SSID and the filter mode to apply.

wlStaticWdsMACAddrTable.name: wlStaticWdsMACAddrTable
wlStaticWdsMACAddrTable.description: Table of statically configured Remote MAC Addresses which are permitted to bridge to the wireless LAN interfaces when the Bridge restriction mode is enabled.

wlStaticWdsMACAddrEntry.name: wlStaticWdsMACAddrEntry
wlStaticWdsMACAddrEntry.description: Table of statically configured Remote MAC Addresses which are permitted to bridge to the wireless LAN interfaces when the Bridge restriction mode is enabled.

wlStaticWdsMACIndex.name: wlStaticWdsMACIndex
wlStaticWdsMACIndex.description: The index into the static WDS Remote MAC Address table for a wireless LAN interface.

wlStaticWdsRemoteMACAddr.name: wlStaticWdsRemoteMACAddr
wlStaticWdsRemoteMACAddr.description: The MAC address that is permitted WDS bridge access to the wireless LAN interface.

wlScanWdsMACAddrTable.name: wlScanWdsMACAddrTable
wlScanWdsMACAddrTable.description: Table of scanned Remote MAC Addresses which are permitted to bridge to the wireless LAN interfaces when the Bridge restriction mode is enabled.

wlScanWdsMACAddrEntry.name: wlScanWdsMACAddrEntry
wlScanWdsMACAddrEntry.description: Table of scanned Remote MAC Addresses which are permitted to bridge to the wireless LAN interfaces when the Bridge restriction mode is enabled.

wlScanWdsMACIndex.name: wlScanWdsMACIndex
wlScanWdsMACIndex.description: The index into the WDS scanned table of Remote MAC Addresses that may access a wireless LAN interface.

wlScanWdsRemoteMACAddr.name: wlScanWdsRemoteMACAddr
wlScanWdsRemoteMACAddr.description: The MAC address previously scanned that is permitted WDS bridge access to the wireless LAN interface.

wlAuthStationsTable.name: wlAuthStationsTable
wlAuthStationsTable.description: Table of authenicated wireless stations and their status information.

wlAuthStationsEntry.name: wlAuthStationsEntry
wlAuthStationsEntry.description: Table of authenicated wireless stations and their status information.

wlAuthStationIndex.name: wlAuthStationIndex
wlAuthStationIndex.description: The index into the Authentication Stations table.

wlAuthStationMACAddr.name: wlAuthStationMACAddr
wlAuthStationMACAddr.description: The MAC address of the authenticated station.

wlAuthStationAssociationStatus.name: wlAuthStationAssociationStatus
wlAuthStationAssociationStatus.description: True if the station has been associated.

wlAuthStationAuthorizationStatus.name: wlAuthStationAuthorizationStatus
wlAuthStationAuthorizationStatus.description: True if the station has been authorized.

wlAuthStationSSID.name: wlAuthStationSSID
wlAuthStationSSID.description: SSID with which the station has authenticated.

wlAuthStationInterface.name: wlAuthStationInterface
wlAuthStationInterface.description: Interface through which the station has authenticated.

zhnWirelessCompliance.name: zhnWirelessCompliance
zhnWirelessCompliance.description: The Compliance statement for SNMP entities which manage the Zhone CPE Wireless Configuration, Status and Statistics Information

zhnWlBaseCfgGroup.name: zhnWlBaseCfgGroup
zhnWlBaseCfgGroup.description: A collection of Zhone Wireless objects that describe the WLAN adapter basic configuration and status information.

zhnWlVirtualCfgGroup.name: zhnWlVirtualCfgGroup
zhnWlVirtualCfgGroup.description: A collection of Zhone Wireless objects that describe the WLAN virtual interface configuration and status information.

zhnWlSecurityGroup.name: zhnWlSecurityGroup
zhnWlSecurityGroup.description: A collection of Zhone Wireless objects that describe the WLAN virtual interface security information.

zhnWlMACFilterGroup.name: zhnWlMACFilterGroup
zhnWlMACFilterGroup.description: A collection of Zhone Wireless objects that describe the WLAN MAC filter rules.

zhnWlStaticWdsMACAddrGroup.name: zhnWlStaticWdsMACAddrGroup
zhnWlStaticWdsMACAddrGroup.description: A collection of Zhone Wireless objects that describe the WLAN statically configured WDS MAC addresses.

zhnWlScanWdsMACAddrGroup.name: zhnWlScanWdsMACAddrGroup
zhnWlScanWdsMACAddrGroup.description: A collection of Zhone Wireless objects that describe the WLAN WDS Scanned MAC addresses.

zhnWlAuthStationsGroup.name: zhnWlAuthStationsGroup
zhnWlAuthStationsGroup.description: A collection of Zhone Wireless objects that indentify the stations that have authenticated with the Access Point.
